# Test coverage (≥90% goal)

Target **≥90% global line coverage** in each repo. Measure with `npm run test:coverage`.

## When changing production code

Include or update Jest tests in the same PR:

| Repo | Paths | Pattern |
| ---- | ----- | ------- |
| Backend | `src/interactions/`, `src/tools/` | DB + fabbrica (`usePrisma()`); GraphQL → mock interactions |
| Frontend | `components/`, `lib/`, `app/` | RTL; mock `@/lib/graphql` hooks |
| Scrapers | `src/scrapers/`, `src/db/` | Fixture HTML/JSON; mock `catalog-dedup/ingest` + Prisma |

## Rules

- Do **not** lower `coverageThreshold` to green CI — add tests or get plan approval for exclusions.
- LLM/agent paths: mock `trackedAgentGenerate`; assert deterministic branches only.
- `catalog-dedup/core` matching logic is tested in the package (≥90%); scrapers/backend test wiring only.
- Before push on coverage-sensitive paths: `npm test` and `npm run test:coverage` in the affected repo.

See `implementationPlans/ALE-25-improve-test-coverage.md`.
